The Game of Thrones Tapestry is a hand woven tapestry which currently stands at 66 m (217 ft) long. Opened to the public on the 21st July 2017 at the Ulster Museum in Belfast, Northern Ireland. Once finished, it will be longer than its inspiration, the Bayeux Tapestry at 77 m (253 ft). The tapestry tells the entire story of the television show, Game of Thrones. Comprised of six 11 metre long panels of hand woven fabric, to which a further seven panels, each 1.5 metres will be added. The six long panels depict scenes from the first six series. As season 7 is aired weekly (in 2017) the tapestry will grow an extra 1.5m to reflect that weeks episode.
